definitions: a gradual reduction of air pressure on a person who has been experiencing high pressure while diving, in order to prevent decompression sickness

examples.text: itching and rashes often occur following decompression
the swim took some two hours, including a one hour decompression stop

shortDefinitions: gradual reduction of air pressure on person who has been experiencing high pressure while diving

definitions: the process of expanding computer data to its normal size so that it can be read by a computer

examples.text: this disk contains a number of utilities which require decompression

shortDefinitions: process of expanding computer data to its normal size so that it can be read by computer

definitions: a surgical procedure that relieves excessive pressure on an internal part of the body such as the cranium or spinal cord.
shortDefinitions: surgical procedure that relieves excessive pressure on internal part of body
